{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877999643,"sessionID":"ses_2856d0f1affeCOzvGfZgcTf2Ts","part":{"id":"prt_d7a93cbe50014sqthnTMIjUJ1I","messageID":"msg_d7a934a87001nwJuF70GYVtWpK","sessionID":"ses_2856d0f1affeCOzvGfZgcTf2Ts","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-acda2f0a90b245ef8a747d4a8e93c9e4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification extends the base AgentCube Python SDK specifications for the `AgentRuntimeClient` component, providing additional acceptance criteria for edge cases, error handling, and configuration scenarios.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Router URL configuration validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that a router URL is available either via argument or environment variable.\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL missing at initialization\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning message about ROUTER_URL not being set\n- **AND** the system SHALL set `self.router_url` to an empty string\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL provided via argument\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router.example.com\"` is provided to `__init__`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n- **AND** no warning SHALL be logged\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set to `\"http://env-router.example.com\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` is called without `router_url` argument\n- **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to `\"http://env-router.example.com\"`\n\n### Requirement: Session ID bootstrap and reuse\n\nThe system SHALL support both bootstrapping a new session ID from the router and reusing an existing session ID.\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap new session ID on initialization\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided to `__init__`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `bootstrap_session_id()` on the data plane client\n- **AND** `self.session_id` SHALL be set to the bootstrapped session ID\n\n#### Scenario: Reuse existing session ID\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is provided to `__init__`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n- **AND** `self.session_id` SHALL be set to `\"existing-session-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID missing response header\n- **GIVEN** the router returns a response without the `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID network failure\n- **GIVEN** the router is unreachable or returns an error status\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `requests.RequestException`\n- **AND** the initialization SHALL fail\n\n### Requirement: Invoke method with session validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that a session ID is initialized before allowing invoke operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with initialized session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"input\": \"test\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST the payload to the data plane endpoint\n- **AND** return the response JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session ID\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty string\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"input\": \"test\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with per-call timeout override\n- **GIVEN** default instance timeout is `120` seconds\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={}, timeout=30.0)` is called\n- **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `30.0` seconds\n- **AND** the connect timeout SHALL remain the instance default\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without per-call timeout\n- **GIVEN** instance timeout is `120` seconds and instance connect_timeout is `5.0` seconds\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n### Requirement: Context manager lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL support the context manager protocol for proper resource cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager enter\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** entering the context (`with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:`)\n- **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit on normal completion\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the context block exits normally\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` on the client\n- **AND** the underlying HTTP session SHALL be closed\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit on exception\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the context block exits due to an exception\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` on the client\n- **AND** the underlying HTTP session SHALL be closed\n- **AND** the exception SHALL propagate normally\n\n### Requirement: Data plane client initialization\n\nThe system SHALL properly initialize the data plane client with the correct configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client receives correct parameters\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL be instantiated with the same `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n- **AND** the data plane client SHALL construct the correct base URL using `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane client default connection pool settings\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized without custom pool settings\n- **WHEN** the data plane client is created\n- **THEN** `pool_connections` SHALL default to `10`\n- **AND** `pool_maxsize` SHALL default to `10`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP session management\n\nThe system SHALL properly manage the underlying HTTP session lifecycle.\n\n#### Scenario: Close method closes HTTP session\n- **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n- **AND** an info log message SHALL be logged\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane close method\n- **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n- **AND** a debug log message SHALL be logged\n\n### Requirement: Verbose logging configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support verbose logging for debugging purposes.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is passed to `__init__`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** the logger level SHALL be set to `DEBUG` (level 10)\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging disabled\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=False` is passed to `__init__` or omitted\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** the logger level SHALL remain at the default `INFO` level\n\n### Requirement: Session header management\n\nThe system SHALL consistently use the `x-agentcube-session-id` header for all Router requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Session header constant\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** accessing the session header name\n- **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL be set to `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called with a valid `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the POST request is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n\n### Requirement: Error handling and propagation\n\nThe system SHALL properly handle and propagate errors from HTTP requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke on non-2xx response\n- **GIVEN** the router returns a status code >= 400\n- **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `response.raise_for_status()`\n- **AND** `requests.HTTPError` SHALL be raised\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap on non-2xx response\n- **GIVEN** the router returns a status code >= 400 during bootstrap\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `response.raise_for_status()`\n- **AND** `requests.HTTPError` SHALL be raised\n\n### Requirement: Type annotations and API contract\n\nThe system SHALL provide proper type annotations for public methods.\n\n#### Scenario: Type annotations present\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` classes\n- **WHEN** inspecting method signatures\n- **THEN** `__init__` SHALL have proper type annotations\n- **AND** `__enter__` SHALL return `\"AgentRuntimeClient\"`\n- **AND** `invoke` SHALL accept `payload: dict[str, object]` and `timeout: float | None`\n- **AND** `invoke` SHALL return `dict[str, object]`\n- **AND** `close` SHALL return `None`\n\n---\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nThis delta specification extends the existing base specifications for the AgentRuntimeClient. All requirements are additive and do not modify existing behavior. The implementation remains fully backward compatible with code that uses the AgentRuntimeClient according to the base design and specification documents.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis delta specification depends on:\n- Base design document: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base specification document: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Python >= 3.10 (as specified in base requirements)\n- `requests` library (as specified in base requirements)\n\n## Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This delta specification defines additional acceptance criteria for the existing AgentRuntimeClient implementation without introducing breaking changes.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [16:25] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\nERROR [18:25] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\nERROR [78:65] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py\">\nERROR [82:24] Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":15,"character":24},"end":{"line":15,"character":25}},"message":"Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer","severity":1,"code":"reportGeneralTypeIssues","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportGeneralTypeIssues"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":17,"character":24},"end":{"line":17,"character":25}},"message":"Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer","severity":1,"code":"reportGeneralTypeIssues","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportGeneralTypeIssues"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":77,"character":64},"end":{"line":77,"character":65}},"message":"Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer","severity":1,"code":"reportGeneralTypeIssues","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportGeneralTypeIssues"}}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":81,"character":23},"end":{"line":81,"character":24}},"message":"Alternative syntax for unions requires Python 3.10 or newer","severity":1,"code":"reportGeneralTypeIssues","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportGeneralTypeIssues"}}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775877999610,"end":1775877999641}}}}
